What is the memory footprint of 1M triangles?
    Example thinking:
    Each triangle:
      3 vertices. Each vertex = 3 doubles (8 bytes each) = 3 × 3 × 8 = 72 bytes
      normal (3 doubles = 24 bytes)
      Total: ~96 bytes per triangle
    1M triangles ≈ 96 MB
    So if you store all the in vector and vector gets full. How that works? (how vector grows internally?)
    Where this memory is stored. In RAM? how much RAM would it takes at 10M then?

